# Pagination

- **Params:** Use query params as defined by the API (e.g. `page`, `size`, `limit`, `offset` or `cursor`). Use `.queryParam("page", 1).queryParam("size", 10)`.
- **Response shape:** Assert the structure (e.g. `content` array, `totalElements`, `totalPages`, or `next` link). Prefer spec-defined field names.
- **Defaults:** Test default page/size when the API defines defaults; assert number of items and total when available.
- **Boundaries:** Optionally test first page, last page, empty result, or invalid page/size (e.g. negative) if the API specifies behavior. One test per scenario.
- **Order:** Do not assume order of items unless the API guarantees it; assert size and presence of expected items when needed.
